-- Nonferrous Metals May Drop 20% on Average in 2012
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-03-06T04:17:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-06/nonferrous-metals-may-drop-20-on-average-in-2012-correct-.html
(Corrects headline, first paragraph to show decline may be
20 percent.)  Nonferrous metals prices may drop by
about 20 percent on average this year, China Minmetals Corp.
president Zhou Zhongshu told reporters today in Beijing.  The company will seek to develop base metal resources
overseas while focusing on minor metals domestically, Zhou said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
